<p>North Korea says South Korea flew drones across the inter-Korean border this week, calling it a violation of its sovereignty and warning of retaliation. South Korea has denied the allegation. The exchange adds fresh strain to already tense inter-Korean relations and complicates Seoul’s stated push to reopen communication channels with Pyongyang.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/DCmce5UiK__sowUIUMl1Vf-izTg_D45v4LktIAk8Wog6D8RzO-YUk3hVBfSXnFmrVJNKEs7jZK7vWKIInqeh3LAskiOssqtJMiNdkpxg7hl7o64-dHSllYezZYwyGHjIEHCnELDXAbD7Ofu5QR5Y2vo__ciB_rSkrzMsq7MUCg' alt='' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Shot-down claim: North Korea said it shot down a South Korean drone over its airspace and claimed the aircraft collected surveillance footage.</li><li>Outreach rebuff: Analysts cited in one report said Pyongyang’s renewed drone allegations may be intended to portray Seoul as a permanent enemy, rather than to address an actual security breach.</li><li>Political timing: The same analysis linked the rhetoric to North Korea’s run-up to a key ruling-party congress, where hard-line messaging can reinforce its stance on inter-Korean hostility.</li><li>“Consequences” warning: North Korea’s military described the alleged drone flights as “unpardonable” and said South Korea would face consequences.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>North Korea (military): Pyongyang says South Korea violated its sovereignty by flying drones into its airspace and warns it will respond. (<a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/north-korea-vows-response-as-it-accuses-the-south-of-flying-drones-across-the-border'>Japan Today</a>)</li><li>South Korea (government): Seoul denies North Korea’s accusation that it flew drones across the border. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/north-korea-accuses-the-south-of-flying-drones-across-the-border/article70493740.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Analysts: Commentators quoted say North Korea’s revived claims appear designed to shut down Seoul’s outreach and cement a narrative of permanently hostile relations. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3339423/north-korea-revives-drone-claims-rebuff-seouls-outreach'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/north-korea-vows-response-as-it-accuses-the-south-of-flying-drones-across-the-border'>North Korea vows response as it accuses the South of flying drones across the border</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/north-korea-accuses-the-south-of-flying-drones-across-the-border/article70493740.ece'>North Korea accuses the South of flying drones across the border</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/north-korea-vows-response-accuses-south-flying-drones-129077683'>North Korea vows response as it accuses the South of flying drones across border</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/north-korea-claims-it-shot-down-south-korean-drone-over-its-airspace/a-75458104'>North Korea claims it shot down South Korean drone over its airspace</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3339423/north-korea-revives-drone-claims-rebuff-seouls-outreach'>North Korea revives drone claims in rebuff to Seoul’s outreach</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>